syntax:

sudo apt-get [options]




---------------------------------------------------------
apt-get it is a debian base command
yum and dnf is for redhat base command
apt -get is comand line tool which work with apt package  manager
apt(advance packging tool) 
use to install and update the packges
----------------------------------------------------------
sudo apt-get update    :poackge resynck with remote
sudo apt-get   install java     :will insatll the software java
sudo apt-get remove java        :will remove software from system.i will not configuration it will remove software only
sudo apt-get remove  --purge java :will remove software and configuration
sudo apt-get autoremove java    :no longer needed packge will removed
